            "title": "Moving into our new Set Direction offices on University Ave; Spying on Sencha",
            "link": "http:\/\/almaer.com\/blog\/moving-into-new-offices",
            "comments": "http:\/\/almaer.com\/blog\/moving-into-new-offices#comments",
            "pubDate": "Tue, 23 Nov 2010 07:46:15 +0000",
            "dc:creator": "dion",
            "category": ["Mobile", "Set Direction", "Tech"],
            "guid": {
                "isPermaLink": "false",
                "content": "http:\/\/almaer.com\/blog\/?p=2885"
            },
            "description": "Today was a big day for us, moving into the new pad on University Avenue, Palo Alto. Not a bad place to be! Major kudos to Spencer Tall of Allegis Capital who are letting us hang with them as we incubate our ideas. It is majorly appreciated, and exciting.\nOnce we finally settled into our offices [...]",
            "content:encoded": "<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http:\/\/setdirection.com\/\"><img src=\"http:\/\/almaer.com\/blog\/uploads\/set-direction-offices.png\" alt=\"Moving into Set Direction Offices\" title=\"Moving into Set Direction Offices\" width=\"521\" height=\"244\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2887\"><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Today was a big day for us, moving into the new pad on University Avenue, Palo Alto. Not a bad place to be! Major kudos to Spencer Tall of Allegis Capital who are letting us hang with them as we incubate our ideas. It is majorly appreciated, and exciting.<\/p>\n<p>Once we finally settled into our offices (after a trip to the Apple Store, just a block away!) we sat down to look at the view, and we giggled to see that it was this:<\/p>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http:\/\/sencha.com\/\"><img src=\"http:\/\/almaer.com\/blog\/uploads\/spying-on-sencha.jpg\" alt=\"Spying on Sencha\" title=\"Spying on Sencha\" width=\"525\" height=\"703\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2889\"><\/a><\/p>\n<p>We are staring at the front door of Sencha! It feels like we are on a stakeout to see when <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http:\/\/notes.sencha.com\/post\/1410909609\/our-ceo-abe-elias-took-the-the-stage-in-front-of\">Abe<\/a> comes and goes. We took this shot and sent it to Abe just to let him know that we are &#8220;in position&#8221; ;)<\/p>\n<p>We said &#8220;hi&#8221; to our Sencha neighbours and man did they seem in good spirits. The very recent <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http:\/\/notes.sencha.com\/post\/1594203751\/lunchtime-at-senchacon\">SenchaCon<\/a> was a huge success. It was there that they announced their 1.0 of Sencha Touch, and that <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http:\/\/www.sencha.com\/blog\/2010\/11\/15\/sencha-touch-1-0-ships-now-free\/\">it was to be free<\/a>. This is great news for the mobile Web community at large. The segment is buzzing with jQuery Mobile, Enyo, Sencha Touch, and more. <\/p>\n<p>Congrats to all, and Abe&#8230;.. looking forward to being your neighbour mate.<\/p>",
