            "title": "HTML5 forms validation in Firefox 4",
            "link": "http:\/\/feedproxy.google.com\/~r\/ajaxian\/~3\/5-nELRScqMY\/html5-forms-validation-in-firefox-4",
            "comments": "http:\/\/ajaxian.com\/archives\/html5-forms-validation-in-firefox-4#comments",
            "pubDate": "Fri, 12 Nov 2010 20:20:34 +0000",
            "dc:creator": "jvaughan",
            "category": ["Firefox", "Front Page", "JavaScript"],
            "guid": {
                "isPermaLink": "false",
                "content": "http:\/\/ajaxian.com\/?p=10463"
            },
            "description": "Mounir Lamouri looks at native browser-side form validation in Firefox4\u00a0 &#8211; while re-iterating the need for re-validating on the server-side too. The objective of the browser-side form validation is to relieve JavaScript of the need to do a lot of basic form checking. Lanouri writes:\n&#8221;All new input types introduced with HTML5 forms except search and [...]",
            "content:encoded": "<p>Mounir Lamouri looks at <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http:\/\/blog.oldworld.fr\/index.php?post\/2010\/11\/17\/HTML5-Forms-Validation-in-Firefox-4\">native browser-side form validation in Firefox4<\/a>\u00a0 &#8211; while re-iterating the need for re-validating on the server-side too. The objective of the browser-side form validation is to relieve JavaScript of the need to do a lot of basic form checking. Lanouri writes:<\/p>\n<blockquote><p>&#8221;All new input types introduced with HTML5 forms except search and tel benefit from internal validation.<br \/>Firefox 4 is going to support email and url and the validation will check if the value is a valid email or url respectively.&#8221;<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p>Also discussed is added pattern matching support and a new pseudo-class that applies on submit controls when a form has an invalid element.<\/p>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http:\/\/feeds.feedburner.com\/~ff\/ajaxian?a=5-nELRScqMY:tJhsmycL2uY:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http:\/\/feeds.feedburner.com\/~ff\/ajaxian?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"><\/a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http:\/\/feeds.feedburner.com\/~ff\/ajaxian?a=5-nELRScqMY:tJhsmycL2uY:7Q72WNTAKBA\"><img src=\"http:\/\/feeds.feedburner.com\/~ff\/ajaxian?d=7Q72WNTAKBA\" border=\"0\"><\/a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http:\/\/feeds.feedburner.com\/~ff\/ajaxian?a=5-nELRScqMY:tJhsmycL2uY:D7DqB2pKExk\"><img src=\"http:\/\/feeds.feedburner.com\/~ff\/ajaxian?i=5-nELRScqMY:tJhsmycL2uY:D7DqB2pKExk\" border=\"0\"><\/a>\n<\/div>",
